message: Initial import

Fixing false friend “styleguide” to “style guide”
Styleguide is common in German language as compounded noun mixing into
English vocabulary. Turns out that there are no “styleguides” in English
language.

[Breaking Change] Fix style guide Git repo URL
Fixing Git repo URL after renaming all instances of “styleguide” to
“style guide”. Please update your Git remote accordingly with
`git remote set-url origin https://github.com/wikimedia/WikimediaUI-Style-Guide.git`.
Bump version to 0.1

Fix incorrect version number

message:
Provide style guide imagery as resource – T167156 (#48)
* resources: Add WikimediaUI-Style-Guide-Imagery Sketch file
* build: Add sketch_export for Style Guide Imagery
Creating Grunt tasks for SVGs and fallback @2x PNGs. Also
renaming falsely labelled other sketch_export task.
Bug: T167156
* build: Introduce `grunt-svgmin` & optimize SVGs
Introducing `grunt-svgmin` to build process and optimizing
all SVGs currently added with all SVGO options but:
 - Round/rewrite number lists (can cause unprecise rendering)
 - Prefer viewbox to width/height (disabled per default)
 - Remove raster images (disabled per default)
 - Remove title (not good for accessibility reasons, disabled per default)
 - Remove viewbox (troubles with some other browsers)
 - Remove XML instructions (disables viewing as standalone file)
Sketch export & svgmin are not part of 'default' task for
build step performance and usage frequency reasons, but are set in their
own 'imagery' task.

build: Updating build steps (CSS) (#67)
- Removing 'css/vendor folder in favor of adding npm modules and
having them import automatically via postcss-import plugin.
- Adding newer version of WikimediaUI Base & normalize.css via npm.
- Fixing 'grunt watch' task to ignore files in the 'css/build' folder
- Adding npm tasks to call Grunt, for those who don't install Grunt globally.
- Downgrading normalize.css to v7 & fixing typo
- Fixing relative paths in CSS URLs & switching minifier to cssnano
- Removing the need for `grunt-contrib-cssmin` since PostCSS can
integrate a minifier.
This means we don't have to output an uncompressed css file in the
`build` folder. Instead we can generate the minified file in one pass,
which also gets rid of the cssmin grunt tasks.
- Also outputting a source map for the minified CSS file.
- Adding seperate grunt tasks for compiling minified and unminifed CSS
  Minified CSS gets compiles with source maps, unminified does not.
